section.def:
application
                (申請) means an application to the Lands Tribunal
            under section 8(2), 19(2) or 33;

claim
                (申索) means a claim for compensation under
                section 18;

claimant
                (申索人) means a person who has made a claim for
            compensation;

paragraph.content:
where an undivided share of a leasehold interest in land has appurtenant to
                    it rights to the exclusive use and occupation of a building or part thereof on
                    such land, such share in the land and all rights appurtenant thereto;

run from the day on which notice of resumption is affixed to the land under
                    that section and in no case expire earlier than 1 month from that day;
                    and

state where and at what times a copy of the order and, where appropriate, a
                    plan of the land may be inspected in pursuance of subsection
                    (2)(b);

describe the land and the easement or right and state that an order
                    creating the easement or right has been made under section
                    6(1);

state where and at what times a copy of the order and a plan of the
                    easement or right may be inspected in pursuance of subsection
                    (2)(b);

the Director of Buildings or the Director of Lands is of the opinion that
                    an emergency exists which necessitates immediate entry;
                    or

the claim being served on the Director within the appropriate period
                    specified in the fourth column of Part I of the First Schedule;
                    and

the nature of the claimant’s interest in the land including in the case of
                    a sub-lessee or sub-tenant his landlord’s name and address and details of the
                    sub-lease or tenancy;

tr.td:
the re-opening of the street or part thereof in the case of a street
                                or part of a street temporarily closed or closed for an indefinite
                                period;

section.def:
disturbance (騷擾) means the displacement of a person from land and the
                    interruption of or interference with trade or business, whether such
                    displacement, interruption or interference is temporary or permanent;

paragraph.content:
in the case of disturbance of a trade or business on any land, the
                            financial loss naturally and reasonably resulting from the disturbance
                            of that trade or business;
